06:36.573 --> 06:40.223
(SAM HUMMING)

06:40.258 --> 06:42.410
Are you gonna be
humming that song all day?

06:42.445 --> 06:44.212
I might be. I like it.

06:44.247 --> 06:46.447
Nick was saying he's getting ready

06:46.483 --> 06:48.549
- for that German test tomorrow.
- Yeah. He's actually doing

06:48.585 --> 06:50.518
- really well in that class.
- I was actually at the library

06:50.553 --> 06:52.553
yesterday and I saw they
had a couple of language CDs.

06:52.589 --> 06:54.389
You might wanna let him know.
He could check them out.

06:54.424 --> 06:57.342
- I will. Thanks.
- Yeah. Oh, Grace?

06:57.378 --> 07:00.561
I noticed the game closet
upstairs is a bit of a mess.

07:00.597 --> 07:02.563
That's true. Gramp and I
tried to play Life

07:02.599 --> 07:04.399
the other day and it was half Monopoly.

07:04.434 --> 07:07.135
Would you mind cleaning it up
and putting things

07:07.170 --> 07:09.147
- back in the right boxes?
- Sure.

07:09.172 --> 07:12.306
Thanks. Thanks for helping
bring that piano out.

07:12.342 --> 07:15.076
Oh... yeah. Well, any time
you need a strong man,

07:15.111 --> 07:17.078
- you know who to call.
- Yes, I do.

07:17.113 --> 07:19.414
(CHUCKLING) Ahem!

07:19.449 --> 07:21.149
OK. Uh...

07:21.184 --> 07:23.618
Is this what it's gonna be like
now that you're engaged?

07:23.653 --> 07:25.687
- Yeah, I think so.
- Pretty much.

07:25.722 --> 07:28.790
Well. Ahem. I just hope no one
writes a song about that.

07:30.760 --> 07:32.994
Have a great day.

07:35.932 --> 07:37.765
Here you go. That artichoke omelette

07:37.801 --> 07:40.435
- was fantastic.
- Oh, I'm so glad you liked it.

07:40.470 --> 07:42.870
I was just coming from
a deposition. I'm not sure I

07:42.906 --> 07:44.772
would've come in if I hadn't
seen the sign outside but, um...

07:44.808 --> 07:47.742
- I'm glad that I did.
- So I'm really glad

07:47.777 --> 07:51.446
I put that sign out there then.
Thank you.

07:55.719 --> 07:58.252
- What are you doing?!
- Uh, working?

07:58.288 --> 08:00.154
That guy was interested in you!

08:00.190 --> 08:02.790
- Who?
- What? You couldn't tell

08:02.826 --> 08:04.625
by the way he was looking at you?

08:04.661 --> 08:06.327
Uh, he was barely looking at me.

08:06.362 --> 08:08.629
So you're not gonna do anything about it?

08:08.665 --> 08:11.599
Abigail, just because a man

08:11.634 --> 08:13.801
speaks to a woman doesn't mean
he's flirting with her.

08:13.837 --> 08:16.137
Well, that's how it works for me.

08:19.809 --> 08:23.177
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

08:24.714 --> 08:27.348
Ooh! How did we manage

08:27.383 --> 08:29.650
to get so much stuff
crammed in this tiny space?

08:29.686 --> 08:32.385
I don't know. I guess it
just filled up over the years.

08:32.422 --> 08:34.322
But it'll be good to try

08:34.357 --> 08:36.857
to put things back the way they were.

08:36.893 --> 08:39.460
- Hmm.
- Sorry. I didn't realize

08:39.496 --> 08:41.662
you guys were in here.
George said I could come up

08:41.698 --> 08:43.397
and look for my library card in here.

08:43.433 --> 08:46.391
- Uh, with the games?
- Yeah. Grace and I used it

08:46.427 --> 08:49.303
as a get-out-of-jail-free card
because I'm the one who's missing.

08:49.339 --> 08:51.506
We played that game
like, over a year ago.

08:51.541 --> 08:53.508
And how often do I need
to go to the library?

08:53.543 --> 08:57.201
My dad told me about the language CDs.

08:57.237 --> 08:59.014
- Thank you.
- Oh. Sure.

08:59.050 --> 09:00.681
Maybe you wanna help Grace

09:00.717 --> 09:02.917
reorganize while you're looking for it?

09:03.526 --> 09:05.686
Oh, I can, uh, probably

09:05.722 --> 09:07.522
get all the work done by myself.

09:07.557 --> 09:09.757
Oh, but it'll go so much faster with two.

09:10.492 --> 09:13.227
I... I can help out. Sure.

09:13.263 --> 09:15.830
Great. I'll get out of your way then.

09:15.865 --> 09:18.032
OK.

09:20.069 --> 09:22.703
So... I'll start working

09:22.739 --> 09:24.772
on the top shelves, and you
can go working on the bottom.

09:24.808 --> 09:26.707
Whatever. Wait.

09:26.743 --> 09:28.709
Why do you get to decide who does what?

09:28.745 --> 09:31.946
- Because what does it matter?
- Because maybe one shelf is going

09:31.981 --> 09:34.382
- to be easier than the other.
- Fine.

09:34.417 --> 09:36.217
Here.

09:36.976 --> 09:39.387
We'll pick a card,
and whoever gets the highest

09:39.422 --> 09:41.722
can choose which shelves they want to do.

09:42.857 --> 09:44.392
OK...

09:49.899 --> 09:52.433
- OK. Well, let me pick.
- Fine.

09:58.915 --> 10:00.274
Two of clubs.

10:00.310 --> 10:03.211
OK, look. I really don't care

10:03.246 --> 10:05.413
who does which shelf,
but just choose one.

10:05.448 --> 10:08.282
Fine. Since you wanted
the top, I'll take the top.

10:08.318 --> 10:11.619
- Fine.
- Unless you only said

10:11.654 --> 10:13.754
you wanted the top to make me
think that's what you wanted

10:13.790 --> 10:16.123
- so I'd fight for it.
- Then you can have the bottom.

10:16.159 --> 10:18.125
Or maybe you knew
I'd want the one you wanted

10:18.161 --> 10:20.761
so you pretended to want the one
you didn't want

10:20.797 --> 10:22.964
so I would want the one
I only thought you wanted.

10:22.999 --> 10:26.100
- So take the top.
- Thank you. I will.

10:35.078 --> 10:38.179
Oh... I guess you picked the wrong one.

10:45.655 --> 10:47.622
- What are you doing?
- Oh, some of the herbs

10:47.657 --> 10:49.490
and spices got mixed up.
I'm just putting them back

10:49.525 --> 10:51.492
- where I can find them.
- Oh, I can do that.

10:51.527 --> 10:53.494
- Oh, well...
- No, seriously. I'm sure

10:53.529 --> 10:55.496
you have more important things to do.

10:55.531 --> 10:57.290
All right. I guess I can
find out what George needs.

10:57.325 --> 10:59.800
- Oh. Is he here?
- Hi, George!

10:59.836 --> 11:04.305
Ah, Cassie! Do you have some springs

11:04.340 --> 11:06.140
that will fit on screen doors?

11:06.175 --> 11:08.142
Abigail asked me to fix the one

11:08.177 --> 11:09.977
at the back of the house
that keeps slamming.

11:10.013 --> 11:11.812
Oh. That's one of those sounds of life

11:11.848 --> 11:13.614
I guess I've just gotten used to.

11:13.650 --> 11:17.184
Well, apparently other people
hear things differently, so...

11:17.220 --> 11:20.821
Well, there is a box
of hardware odds and ends

11:20.857 --> 11:22.823
over there if you'd like to take a look.

11:22.859 --> 11:24.709
- Great. Thanks.
- Sure.

11:26.562 --> 11:28.829
(GEORGE HUMMING)

11:35.778 --> 11:37.248
That's a nice song.

11:37.284 --> 11:39.840
Oh.

11:39.876 --> 11:41.842
I didn't even realize I was humming.

11:43.269 --> 11:44.979
Did you find what you were looking for?

11:45.014 --> 11:47.348
No, which is odd

11:47.383 --> 11:50.351
because you usually have
what everybody needs.

11:50.386 --> 11:52.853
- Can't win 'em all.
- Well, I'll see you at home.

11:52.889 --> 11:54.822
All right. Oh, Sam invited me

11:54.857 --> 11:56.991
to dinner, so I'll
probably be home after that.

11:57.026 --> 11:58.726
OK. I guess I'll know when you come in

11:58.761 --> 12:01.162
- when that screen door slams.
- I'll try not to make

12:01.197 --> 12:03.164
- too much noise.
- (BOTH CHUCKLING)

12:03.199 --> 12:05.166
(SOFT MUSIC)

12:05.201 --> 12:07.335
♪♪♪

12:13.910 --> 12:16.010
These are the specials
off the top. Your server will be

12:16.045 --> 12:18.212
with you in a minute.

12:22.485 --> 12:24.919
- There's the happy couple!
- Right now, we are

12:24.954 --> 12:26.721
only the hungry couple.

12:26.756 --> 12:28.889
- So how about a table for two?
- Right this way.

12:28.925 --> 12:30.891
I'm starving.

12:30.927 --> 12:33.227
- Oh, Stephanie! Hey!
- Oh, hey!

12:33.262 --> 12:35.229
Are you here on a date?

12:35.264 --> 12:37.431
No. I was here to meet Abigail

12:37.467 --> 12:39.467
for a drink, but... she can't make it,

12:39.502 --> 12:42.036
which is fine. I have
lots of errands to run.

12:42.071 --> 12:43.571
- We'll see you later.
- See you.

12:43.606 --> 12:46.874
- Bye.
- Excuse me. I couldn't tell

12:46.909 --> 12:48.909
if you were waiting for someone,
or if you were...

12:48.945 --> 12:52.413
Yeah. I was, but she can't make it.

12:52.448 --> 12:54.915
Well, if you'd like
to join me and the gang

12:54.951 --> 12:56.917
from the fire station,
there's room at our table.

12:56.953 --> 12:59.587
No. That reminds me,

12:59.622 --> 13:02.256
I wanted to stop at the hardware store

13:02.291 --> 13:05.593
and pick up a new garden hose.
Thanks for the offer!

13:05.628 --> 13:08.129
Thanks.

13:08.164 --> 13:10.297
You got a new guitar player,

13:10.333 --> 13:12.400
and she's playing the Haywood song.

13:12.435 --> 13:14.969
- Yeah. It's her first night.
- Oh.

13:15.004 --> 13:16.971
I always like it
when you have music here.

13:17.006 --> 13:19.006
I aim to please.

13:19.042 --> 13:21.742
(ALL CHUCKLING)

13:21.778 --> 13:24.612
So how long has your car
been running slowly?

13:24.647 --> 13:26.614
Oh, is there something wrong with it?

13:26.649 --> 13:28.546
It's just on the way here,
it wasn't accelerating

13:28.581 --> 13:30.898
- as quickly as it could.
- Hmm. Well, maybe that's

13:30.933 --> 13:33.788
because I'm not in as big
of a hurry as you are.

13:33.823 --> 13:36.290
I think if you'd let me

13:36.325 --> 13:38.959
replace your fuel filter,
you could tell the difference.

13:39.636 --> 13:41.462
It's no bother.

13:42.999 --> 13:46.333
♪♪♪

13:52.008 --> 13:53.974
Hello, Courtney.

13:54.010 --> 13:57.385
Hey. Is Grace around?

13:57.420 --> 14:00.948
Yes. She is upstairs,
sorting through games with Nick.

14:00.983 --> 14:02.683
- Nick is here?
- Yes.

14:02.718 --> 14:04.985
Uh... never mind.

14:05.912 --> 14:07.388
We've been avoiding each other

14:07.423 --> 14:09.390
ever since he broke up with me.

14:09.425 --> 14:12.432
Oh. Well, when I see him,

14:12.467 --> 14:14.195
I'll be sure to tell him
how great you looked.

14:14.230 --> 14:16.831
Make sure that you do.

14:16.866 --> 14:18.632
- Courtney.
- Hey.

14:18.668 --> 14:21.001
- Hi. You here to see Grace?
- Uh... I was,

14:21.037 --> 14:24.138
- but she's with Nick.
- Oh.

14:24.173 --> 14:25.390
Yeah.

14:25.415 --> 14:28.075
But, I'm glad you stopped by.

14:28.111 --> 14:32.346
I saw a book and it reminded me of you.

14:34.884 --> 14:37.017
It's about a girl

14:37.053 --> 14:39.220
who has to stay at the hospital,

14:39.255 --> 14:41.922
but she gets through it with the help

14:41.958 --> 14:43.858
of a monster named Courage.

14:43.893 --> 14:46.060
It's got beautiful artwork inside.

14:46.095 --> 14:49.263
Oh, it looks great. Thank you.

14:49.298 --> 14:51.699
- You're welcome.
- I'll see you later.

14:51.734 --> 14:53.567
OK.

14:55.404 --> 14:57.371
So, how was your date with Sam?

14:57.406 --> 15:01.075
- It was good.
- What'd you guys talk about?

15:01.110 --> 15:04.078
Um... date things?

15:04.113 --> 15:06.046
So nothing... special?

15:06.082 --> 15:10.050
No. We had a really nice time
just being together.

15:11.487 --> 15:13.721
Well, if that's
all you want out of life...

15:20.864 --> 15:23.632
How did four different puzzles
get into two boxes?

15:23.667 --> 15:25.333
I don't know,

15:25.369 --> 15:28.837
but I can't tell if this
is the horse or the candy shop.

15:29.774 --> 15:32.340
There isn't a puzzle of a horse
in a candy shop, is there?

15:32.376 --> 15:35.043
- No.
- Well, there should be.

15:41.051 --> 15:43.752
You're not even looking at the pieces.

15:43.787 --> 15:45.720
- Hmm?
- How are you

15:45.756 --> 15:47.856
getting these all right?

15:47.891 --> 15:51.026
It's easy. See, these pieces

15:51.061 --> 15:54.229
are thicker than the other ones.
The pieces for the horse

15:54.264 --> 15:56.364
are smaller than the ones
for the candy shop.

15:56.400 --> 15:58.400
Oh, so you're not magic.

15:58.435 --> 16:00.535
No.

16:00.570 --> 16:02.370
Sometimes I wonder. I mean,

16:02.406 --> 16:04.706
you never freak out
if we have a pop quiz,

16:04.741 --> 16:06.841
almost like you know
they're gonna happen.

16:06.877 --> 16:11.279
- I'll let you in on a secret.
- I study.

16:11.314 --> 16:14.683
Are you telling me
I could have that power too?

16:14.718 --> 16:16.451
Yep. And you wouldn't even need a wand.

16:16.486 --> 16:19.421
- I still might want a wand.
- I know.

16:19.456 --> 16:22.223
Wands are really cool, right? OK.

16:22.259 --> 16:24.693
I think I'm done

16:24.728 --> 16:26.561
with my half.

16:27.303 --> 16:29.097
- Already?
- Yeah.

16:29.132 --> 16:31.566
I haven't even found my library card yet.

16:35.105 --> 16:37.238
♪♪♪

16:40.444 --> 16:44.779
- How did that get there?!
- Oh, it must have been magic.

16:55.759 --> 16:57.926
♪♪♪

17:00.964 --> 17:03.498
(HUMMING)

17:08.338 --> 17:10.405
Hello, Sam.

17:10.440 --> 17:13.441
Good morning. Do you know
anywhere that sells roses?

17:13.477 --> 17:15.443
I have dozens.

17:15.479 --> 17:18.346
- I just need one.
- But I said, "I have dozens."

17:18.381 --> 17:21.449
I just want Cassie to know
I was thinking about her.

17:21.484 --> 17:23.451
Well, if you ask me, a guy should do

17:23.487 --> 17:25.819
more thinking than that, but OK.

17:27.557 --> 17:29.958
(HUMMING)

17:35.499 --> 17:38.633
You know what? You're right.
Make it a dozen.

17:38.668 --> 17:41.136
I might have to start
calling you Mr. Romance.

17:41.171 --> 17:43.338
You know, I'm actually a doctor.

17:43.373 --> 17:45.518
I'm not gonna call you Dr. Romance.

17:45.553 --> 17:48.376
- No. That'd be creepy.
- Mm-hmm.

17:49.780 --> 17:52.046
(SAXOPHONE MUSIC)

17:52.082 --> 17:55.183
♪♪♪

18:01.391 --> 18:03.158
Hi, Martha.

18:03.193 --> 18:06.494
(SCREAMING) Oh! Sam, I am so sorry.

18:06.530 --> 18:08.363
I was just coming from Salt Creek Bridge,

18:08.398 --> 18:11.466
where I finally might've
gotten some inspiration

18:11.501 --> 18:13.968
- for the rededication.
- Well, I'm sure the bridge will

18:14.004 --> 18:15.837
- appreciate a pat on the back.
- Well, I just hope

18:15.872 --> 18:18.673
that what I've come up with
will compare favourably

18:18.708 --> 18:20.809
to the speech my husband gave.

18:20.844 --> 18:23.077
Wow. This song sure is
getting to be popular.

18:23.113 --> 18:25.814
Hmm? Oh!

18:27.551 --> 18:29.517
Yes. You know, I'm hardly listening.

18:29.553 --> 18:31.352
When I'm reading my speech to myself,

18:31.388 --> 18:33.822
all I can hear is my internal voice.

18:33.857 --> 18:35.392
Oh, yeah. When do you have to give that?

18:35.427 --> 18:37.692
Too soon. Ah, the date

18:37.727 --> 18:39.527
is approaching like a Mack truck.

18:39.563 --> 18:41.396
Oh, I'm glad you said that.
I need to stop by the auto parts

18:41.431 --> 18:44.199
store and get a fuel filter
for Cassie's car.

18:44.234 --> 18:46.534
Oh, my goodness! Flowers
and you're fixing her car?

18:46.570 --> 18:49.337
- Girl's gotta drive.
- Yes...

18:49.372 --> 18:51.339
right over that bridge,

18:51.374 --> 18:53.875
which deserves far greater eloquence

18:53.910 --> 18:56.511
than what I've come up with
in my first draft.

18:56.546 --> 18:58.546
Well, let's just hope
that inspiration hits me

18:58.582 --> 19:00.715
before that truck does.

19:00.750 --> 19:03.551
- All right. I'll see you later.
- Mm-hmm!

19:03.587 --> 19:06.087
♪♪♪

19:12.095 --> 19:15.430
Grace, did you and Nick

19:15.465 --> 19:17.565
finish sorting through the game closet?

19:17.601 --> 19:19.567
I did. I finished my half,

19:19.603 --> 19:21.569
but Nick still has
a few more things to do.

19:21.605 --> 19:23.571
How did you finish your job so quickly?

19:23.607 --> 19:25.573
I don't know.

19:25.609 --> 19:27.542
I guess we Merriwick

19:27.577 --> 19:29.744
just know how to make things
happen the way we want them to.

19:29.779 --> 19:32.313
Good for you.

19:34.043 --> 19:37.285
Well, um, I wanted you to work together.

19:37.320 --> 19:38.662
It's not my fault

19:38.697 --> 19:41.389
that he's not as good
at puzzle-sorting as I am.

19:41.424 --> 19:42.790
Hmm.

19:43.593 --> 19:45.126
All done!

19:46.039 --> 19:48.429
Don't you just love it
when you can sit back

19:48.465 --> 19:50.262
and appreciate the way
your work comes together?

19:50.298 --> 19:51.716
Yeah.

19:52.335 --> 19:54.936
Especially after watching
every piece of the puzzle

19:54.971 --> 19:57.772
- fall into place.
- George!

19:57.807 --> 20:00.108
You still working this late?

20:00.143 --> 20:02.443
Yeah. I noticed the baseboards

20:02.479 --> 20:04.812
outside Abigail's room needed sanding,

20:04.848 --> 20:06.614
so I decided to touch up the whole house.

20:06.650 --> 20:09.784
- That's a lot of baseboards.
- Yeah, and they're not gonna

20:09.819 --> 20:11.986
sand themselves, so I decided

20:12.022 --> 20:15.123
I'd get to bed so I can
get up early. Goodnight.

20:15.158 --> 20:17.292
- (ABIGAIL): Night.
- (GRACE): Night.

20:17.327 --> 20:19.627
You can't make baseboards
sand themselves, can you?

20:19.663 --> 20:22.374
No... but that'd be better

20:22.410 --> 20:24.619
than any card trick I've ever done.

20:24.654 --> 20:27.043
Just don't let anyone know your secrets.

20:29.973 --> 20:31.873
- This one?
- Yeah.

20:31.908 --> 20:34.375
♪♪♪

20:44.012 --> 20:46.446
Oh, Sam! There you are.
I have an emergency.

20:46.482 --> 20:49.616
- Are you hurt?
- What? Oh, no, no, no, no!

20:49.651 --> 20:51.985
It's something
much more serious than that.

20:52.020 --> 20:54.821
It's about the bridge dedication.

20:55.738 --> 20:58.258
- Ah.
- I want to highlight

20:58.293 --> 21:01.161
someone who drives
across that bridge every day

21:01.196 --> 21:03.463
and I thought, "Who better
than our own good doctor

21:03.499 --> 21:05.966
who takes that route
on the way to the hospital?"

21:06.001 --> 21:08.468
A lot of people drive across
that bridge every day.

21:08.504 --> 21:10.170
Yes, well...

21:10.205 --> 21:12.472
but none of them are as eloquent as you.

21:12.508 --> 21:15.475
Ah, so you're using flattery.

21:16.717 --> 21:18.345
Well, go on!

21:18.380 --> 21:21.815
Oh! Uh... well... you would be
in very distinguished company!

21:21.850 --> 21:25.018
I've lined up also two state senators

21:25.053 --> 21:26.473
and I've left word for the governor.

21:26.508 --> 21:29.320
Plus, the architect
of the bridge and the son

21:29.355 --> 21:32.392
of the man who poured
the very first concrete pillar.

21:32.427 --> 21:35.162
Hmm. That's a lot of speakers.
It might not leave

21:35.197 --> 21:37.864
- much time for you.
- Well, as you know,

21:37.900 --> 21:40.834
I've never been one for the spotlight.

21:42.371 --> 21:45.505
I appreciate the offer,
but I'm going to pass.

21:45.541 --> 21:48.675
But how am I gonna fill those minutes?

21:48.710 --> 21:50.510
I guess you're just gonna
have to put yourself

21:50.546 --> 21:53.513
- right back in that spotlight!
- Well, at this rate,

21:53.549 --> 21:56.216
I'll be standing up there
without anything to say!

21:56.251 --> 21:58.518
At least the lighting will be good.

21:58.554 --> 22:01.188
Fine. Thank you for being

22:01.223 --> 22:03.523
of absolutely no help whatsoever.

22:03.559 --> 22:06.526
- I do what I can.
- Hmm!

22:06.562 --> 22:08.528
So...

22:08.564 --> 22:10.530
I saw Sam working on your car last night.

22:10.566 --> 22:13.500
Yeah. He decided that's
something he wanted to do.

22:14.530 --> 22:17.037
And yesterday he came in
and bought you a dozen roses.

22:17.072 --> 22:18.705
It was nice to know
he was thinking about me.

22:18.740 --> 22:21.942
It seems like you're on his
mind a lot, more so than usual.

22:21.978 --> 22:24.317
Well, you know, we are engaged.

22:24.352 --> 22:26.179
Yeah. That changes things, doesn't it?

22:26.215 --> 22:29.249
Yeah. So far, it's been pretty good.

22:30.749 --> 22:32.219
If you say so.

22:34.456 --> 22:36.556
I thought we were getting this to share.

22:36.592 --> 22:39.359
Yeah, except you ordered it.

22:39.967 --> 22:41.561
You can help yourself!

22:41.597 --> 22:43.668
I don't really like cheesecake.

22:43.703 --> 22:46.466
Oh. You should have said something.

22:46.501 --> 22:48.268
OK. If you ladies need anything else,

22:48.303 --> 22:50.871
Jennifer will take care of you.
I'm going shopping

22:50.906 --> 22:53.073
for something to wear
on my date tomorrow night.

22:53.108 --> 22:55.775
- You have a date?
- With who?!

22:55.811 --> 22:57.811
A tennis pro. He came in

22:57.846 --> 22:59.713
for a protein shake. We started talking

22:59.748 --> 23:01.514
and then he just asked me out.

23:01.550 --> 23:03.917
Just like that lawyer
who was in here the other day.

23:03.952 --> 23:05.986
And there was a fireman

23:06.021 --> 23:08.455
coming onto you at Liam's.

23:08.490 --> 23:12.092
Yeah... I... guess
that was what was happening.

23:12.127 --> 23:14.828
Anyway, I'm just happy
I figured it out in time

23:14.863 --> 23:16.830
- to say yes to this one.
- Have a good time.

23:16.865 --> 23:19.266
Oh, I plan to.

23:22.968 --> 23:24.437
What?

23:24.473 --> 23:26.072
Didn't you date a lawyer,

23:26.108 --> 23:27.841
a fireman and a tennis pro?

23:28.390 --> 23:30.477
I've dated lots of guys.

23:30.512 --> 23:31.778
So it's just a coincidence

23:31.813 --> 23:34.281
that three men with those same jobs

23:34.316 --> 23:36.616
wanna go out with Stephanie
at the same time?

23:36.652 --> 23:39.486
I can't control what men do.

23:41.278 --> 23:43.623
Are you sure you don't want any of this?

23:43.659 --> 23:45.859
It's really good.

23:48.643 --> 23:50.977
♪♪♪

23:55.323 --> 23:57.534
Tonight?

23:57.535 --> 24:00.329
Oh... you mean right now!

24:00.364 --> 24:02.331
Well, I might be able to make that work

24:02.366 --> 24:04.051
if I can get Tara to close for me.

24:04.086 --> 24:07.503
- Yeah!
- Yeah. I'll meet you there.

24:07.538 --> 24:09.905
I can't wait to see you either.

24:09.941 --> 24:12.007
Sam wants to meet me for dinner.

24:12.043 --> 24:14.009
- Awesome! Have a good time.
- Thanks.

24:14.045 --> 24:16.345
Um... there were a couple of things

24:16.380 --> 24:17.859
I wanted to finish before I go...

24:17.894 --> 24:20.483
- Oh, I can get things done.
- OK.

24:20.518 --> 24:21.992
Oh, by the way,

24:21.993 --> 24:25.394
should Himalayan pink salt
go under H, P, or S?

24:25.430 --> 24:28.197
- Go where?
- I decided to alphabetize

24:28.233 --> 24:30.700
all the spices after I
separated them from the herbs.

24:30.735 --> 24:34.203
Oh. Well, all I needed was for
them not to be mixed together.

24:34.239 --> 24:36.839
I know, but this way,
everything's easier to find.

24:37.334 --> 24:39.842
Unless it's Himalayan pink salt.

24:39.877 --> 24:43.512
Well, I will find
the right place for that.

24:43.548 --> 24:46.215
- Good. Have fun at dinner.
- Thank you!

24:46.251 --> 24:48.584
(DOORBELL RINGING)

24:50.889 --> 24:52.722
What's going on?

24:52.757 --> 24:54.357
My mom wants us to take

24:54.392 --> 24:56.192
some of the toys that we
don't need to the hospital.

24:56.645 --> 24:58.327
Can't you do that yourself?

24:58.363 --> 25:00.329
I could, except my mom said,

25:00.365 --> 25:02.531
"Would you and Nick?" So...

25:02.567 --> 25:04.100
Fine.

25:04.135 --> 25:08.537
- Tomorrow after school?
- Yeah. It'll be fun.

25:08.573 --> 25:11.007
(SIGHING)

25:14.078 --> 25:16.545
♪♪♪

25:30.094 --> 25:32.061
- There you are!
- Hi.

25:32.096 --> 25:33.896
Right on time.

25:33.931 --> 25:36.632
I saved you a spot and ordered
a couple of Belgian ales.

25:36.668 --> 25:38.901
- Oh. I was thinking white wine.
- Well, I can

25:38.936 --> 25:40.736
- get you one of those instead.
- No, no.

25:40.772 --> 25:42.905
- That's fine. This is good.
- Hey, Cassie.

25:42.940 --> 25:44.907
- Hi.
- Can I get you a table?

25:44.942 --> 25:47.076
Um... maybe,

25:47.111 --> 25:49.412
but I think we might wanna dance first,

25:49.447 --> 25:52.648
- before we get settled in.
- Oh, excuse me. We're dancing.

25:52.684 --> 25:54.750
Yeah, go for it.

25:56.354 --> 25:59.955
Ah... When did they start
having dancing in here?

25:59.991 --> 26:01.924
I don't know, but I'm glad they do.

26:01.959 --> 26:03.926
- Mm-hmm.
- Maybe we should

26:03.961 --> 26:06.595
hire these guys to play
our wedding reception.

26:06.631 --> 26:09.265
I didn't realize you were
thinking that far ahead.

26:09.300 --> 26:11.567
Well, we might as well,

26:11.602 --> 26:13.936
so the date doesn't get here too fast.

26:14.681 --> 26:17.640
Except, um... we don't have one yet.

26:17.675 --> 26:20.943
Maybe we should be
thinking about that too.

26:20.978 --> 26:24.814
(BOTH CHUCKLING)

26:32.990 --> 26:35.124
♪♪♪

26:44.836 --> 26:47.136
- Hello, Stephanie.
- Oh, hey!

26:47.171 --> 26:48.904
Do you have any chrysanthemums?
I'm gonna put them

26:48.940 --> 26:51.707
- on the tables at the Bistro.
- Ooh! That'll make the place

26:51.743 --> 26:53.809
- look bright and romantic.
- Oh, well...

26:53.845 --> 26:57.213
I guess I'm just in a bright
and romantic mood.

26:57.248 --> 26:58.871
- They're in the back.
- OK.

27:00.351 --> 27:03.018
- Stephanie!
- Carl!

27:03.054 --> 27:05.154
I... guess

27:05.189 --> 27:06.922
this is going to ruin the surprise, but I

27:06.958 --> 27:09.959
came in here to get flowers
for you, for our date tonight.

27:09.994 --> 27:12.995
Well, I will try and act like
I don't know they're coming.

27:13.030 --> 27:14.964
I'd appreciate that.

27:14.999 --> 27:18.000
Here you go! And I have
plenty, so if you need mo...

27:18.035 --> 27:20.302
Oh. Hi.

27:20.338 --> 27:22.371
Abigail, hello.

27:23.125 --> 27:24.640
Do you two know each other?

27:24.675 --> 27:26.642
Abigail and I dated a couple times.

27:26.677 --> 27:29.555
Did we? I mean, I guess we did.

27:29.590 --> 27:32.681
I've been trying to move up
the tennis rankings since then.

27:32.717 --> 27:35.017
In fact, actually, those protein shakes

27:35.052 --> 27:37.052
you started serving
are part of my training diet.

27:37.604 --> 27:40.061
Protein shakes.

27:40.096 --> 27:42.057
You mean the ones that Abigail suggested

27:42.093 --> 27:44.927
I start serving in order to get
more people into the Bistro?

27:44.962 --> 27:47.029
There are plenty of reasons
to come into the Bistro.

27:47.064 --> 27:50.699
Right. Like having an artichoke omelette.

27:50.735 --> 27:52.568
Something else you told me
to start serving.

27:52.603 --> 27:54.570
And I was there to meet you

27:54.605 --> 27:56.705
at the Brewery that night
that I met the fireman.

27:56.741 --> 27:59.041
Wait. Are you dating a fireman?

27:59.076 --> 28:01.076
No, but I bet you Abigail did.

28:01.112 --> 28:03.679
OK, so I dated that guy once or twice.

28:03.714 --> 28:06.048
- Seven times.
- OK. You know what?

28:06.083 --> 28:08.083
You can cancel our date.

28:08.504 --> 28:11.387
And if you decide to send
any more of your exes my way,

28:11.798 --> 28:14.423
you can tell them I'm not interested.

28:19.890 --> 28:22.064
Can I get some tulips?

28:22.099 --> 28:23.899
Why? She just canceled your date.

28:23.935 --> 28:27.036
Yeah, but I'm having lunch
with my mother, so...

28:28.840 --> 28:31.073
- Thank you so much.
- Thank you!

28:31.108 --> 28:33.075
Have a nice day.

28:33.110 --> 28:34.977
Hello, Martha!

28:35.012 --> 28:37.213
Forget the small talk.
I'm running out of time.

28:37.248 --> 28:40.149
I'm looking for inspiration
for my speech, and since you

28:40.184 --> 28:43.080
always seem to lead me to
the exact thing that I need...

28:44.081 --> 28:46.622
- Where is it?
- Well, what is it you're looking for?

28:46.657 --> 28:48.824
Well, how should I know?
That's why I came to you.

28:49.253 --> 28:52.595
It's hard for one person
to know what inspires another.

28:52.630 --> 28:55.397
Oh, I see. So that's
how you're gonna play this,

28:55.433 --> 28:57.099
is it? All right.

28:57.134 --> 28:59.568
Fine. Oh! How about this?

28:59.604 --> 29:03.105
- Something to light my way?
- Martha...

29:03.140 --> 29:05.107
Oh, but you're smiling, so maybe

29:05.142 --> 29:08.110
it's the right colour,
just not the right thing.

29:08.145 --> 29:10.112
Um... oh!

29:10.147 --> 29:13.115
How about this...

29:13.150 --> 29:15.117
Ecuadorian night cream?

29:15.152 --> 29:18.287
Really? Are you my inspiration?

29:18.322 --> 29:20.523
Oh, goodness. I hope not. It's got

29:20.558 --> 29:22.625
royal bee jelly in it, and anything bees

29:22.660 --> 29:24.960
makes my face break out
like a patchwork quilt.

29:24.996 --> 29:27.129
Um... Let me see.

29:27.164 --> 29:30.132
Oh! How about this?

29:30.167 --> 29:32.067
Uh, or maybe...

29:32.103 --> 29:34.136
whatever this is?

29:34.171 --> 29:36.305
Now, don't play games with me!

29:36.340 --> 29:38.340
I need inspiration and I need it now!

29:38.376 --> 29:40.976
Martha, I wish I could
be of more help, but...

29:41.012 --> 29:43.479
Ugh! Honestly! Well, just forget it then.

29:43.514 --> 29:46.148
You're of absolutely
no help to me whatsoever.

29:46.975 --> 29:49.151
What's that?

29:49.186 --> 29:52.054
Oh. What is that doing there?

29:52.089 --> 29:55.824
It's pink Himalayan salt. It's
usually inside with the spices.

29:55.860 --> 29:58.160
Is that the healthier than regular stuff?

29:58.195 --> 30:00.696
- It is much better.
- Well, Tom is supposed

30:00.731 --> 30:03.832
to be cutting down. So, I'll
just assume that this is a gift,

30:03.868 --> 30:06.835
since the rest of my trip
was a complete wash-out.

30:13.210 --> 30:15.010
Where do these go?

30:15.046 --> 30:17.646
Just taking it down to the kids' ward.

30:17.682 --> 30:19.381
Can't we just leave these at the front?

30:19.417 --> 30:22.184
It's just at the bottom of the stairs.

30:22.219 --> 30:24.097
Grace!

30:25.423 --> 30:27.323
- Courtney!
- Hey!

30:27.358 --> 30:29.191
What are you doing here?

30:29.226 --> 30:31.360
I was just reading this book
to some of the kids.

30:31.395 --> 30:34.196
- Well, Nick and I were just...
- Nick's here?

30:35.567 --> 30:37.433
Courtney?

30:40.037 --> 30:41.837
Hey.

30:41.872 --> 30:43.906
Hey.

30:50.810 --> 30:52.209
So...

30:53.613 --> 30:56.247
Yeah. I'm gonna go.

30:56.282 --> 30:58.750
Wait. Courtney. Courtney, wait!

30:58.785 --> 31:00.284
What?

31:00.320 --> 31:02.286
There's something I wanna say to you.

31:02.322 --> 31:04.255
Something you wanna say to me now?

31:04.290 --> 31:06.224
I think the time to have said something

31:06.259 --> 31:08.593
is when you decided
you wanted to break up with me,

31:08.628 --> 31:11.596
and you said... let me think. Nothing!

31:11.631 --> 31:14.799
I know. You're right, and I'm sorry.

31:14.834 --> 31:16.483
Uh-huh.

31:19.472 --> 31:21.272
Look...

31:21.307 --> 31:23.274
the way things ended between us...

31:24.855 --> 31:27.411
I don't blame you if you hate me.

31:28.114 --> 31:30.948
I screwed up. You're an amazing person

31:30.984 --> 31:35.286
and you deserved better from me.
I really like you.

31:35.321 --> 31:38.756
It's just I wasn't
ready to get more serious.

31:38.792 --> 31:41.125
And that was my problem,

31:41.161 --> 31:42.694
not yours.

31:42.729 --> 31:44.696
And I should have told you that
straight up before I said

31:44.731 --> 31:48.014
- anything to anybody else.
- Yeah, you should've.

31:49.002 --> 31:50.635
(SIGHING)

31:50.670 --> 31:52.602
But at least you're saying it now.

31:53.173 --> 31:55.006
I'm really sorry...

31:55.564 --> 31:57.141
for everything.

32:07.420 --> 32:08.744
Ahem.

32:09.522 --> 32:12.323
That was... good,

32:12.358 --> 32:14.458
what you said.

32:14.958 --> 32:19.129
I mean, that was... good.

32:19.164 --> 32:21.298
Yeah.

32:21.333 --> 32:23.667
That's exactly what I would've
said if I had the chance

32:23.702 --> 32:25.836
to back then but I didn't,
because you got in the middle

32:25.871 --> 32:27.846
of it and messed it all up.

32:29.875 --> 32:32.008
Let's just drop these off and go.

32:34.680 --> 32:37.013
(GRACE SIGHING)

32:37.049 --> 32:39.182
♪♪♪

32:42.387 --> 32:45.222
Oh. What are you doing here?
Trying to dump another one

32:45.257 --> 32:48.759
- of your exes on me?
- No. I came to explain.

32:48.794 --> 32:51.361
What? How I need someone
like you to set me up

32:51.396 --> 32:53.597
because I can't get a guy
to like me on my own?

32:53.632 --> 32:55.832
OK. First of all,
each of those guys did like you.

32:55.868 --> 32:57.939
I may have done some things
to get them to notice you,

32:57.964 --> 32:59.980
but they're the ones
who wanted to ask you out.

33:00.026 --> 33:02.272
Right, because I'm so irresistible.

33:02.308 --> 33:04.508
I was counting on the fact that you were.

33:05.592 --> 33:08.378
Look, I know it's hard,
but after a breakup,

33:08.413 --> 33:10.580
what you need to do is get
right back up on the horse.

33:11.264 --> 33:12.849
Unless you just broke up with a cowboy

33:12.885 --> 33:14.976
because that would just
bring up bad memories.

33:18.123 --> 33:20.891
I know what you were trying to do, and...

33:20.926 --> 33:23.393
well, it was actually kind of nice.

33:23.428 --> 33:25.262
See? I can do that sometimes.

33:25.297 --> 33:27.864
And it does feel good
to know that there are options

33:27.900 --> 33:30.400
out there... when I'm ready.

33:30.435 --> 33:33.703
You're gonna have no trouble
being with whoever you want.

33:33.739 --> 33:35.939
- Thanks.
- Excuse me, I was wondering

33:35.974 --> 33:38.408
if you're going to be here
at the restaurant

33:38.443 --> 33:41.411
- later tonight?
- Oh... um...

33:41.446 --> 33:44.614
It's really sweet of you to ask,

33:44.650 --> 33:46.550
but, um, I'm just not looking

33:46.585 --> 33:48.785
to be with anyone right now, so...

33:48.821 --> 33:51.760
Oh, no. I'm the repairman
for the ice machine.

33:51.796 --> 33:53.957
I just wanted to bring
the parts back later,

33:53.992 --> 33:56.348
- and get you running again.
- Oh...

33:56.383 --> 33:58.595
Right. Ice.

33:58.630 --> 34:01.492
- You know what? Tonight is great.
- Great. See you then.

34:01.527 --> 34:03.600
- I'm gonna see you then!
- Yup.

34:09.541 --> 34:11.507
Oh! I was just about to order

34:11.543 --> 34:13.610
- without you.
- Well, you might as well.

34:13.645 --> 34:15.779
I don't think I'll be eating a thing.

34:15.813 --> 34:17.781
Oh, here. I found this at Cassie's.

34:17.815 --> 34:19.850
It's so your heart doesn't explode.

34:19.885 --> 34:22.819
Thanks. Why is it pink?

34:22.855 --> 34:25.455
Apparently, it's healthier that way.

34:25.489 --> 34:27.424
This makes me think
about the time I dedicated

34:27.458 --> 34:30.793
- the Salt Creek Bridge.
- Yes, which is what has been

34:30.829 --> 34:32.629
on my mind all week.

34:32.664 --> 34:35.665
I'm supposed to rededicate it
this weekend.

34:35.701 --> 34:37.467
Really?

34:37.502 --> 34:39.335
Why didn't you mention that to me?

34:39.371 --> 34:41.638
Because I wanted to wait until
I could come up with something

34:41.672 --> 34:43.473
that was as memorable as what you said.

34:44.315 --> 34:45.507
When I was younger,

34:45.543 --> 34:48.478
I used to think that bridges
were built for going away,

34:48.945 --> 34:50.347
but now I know

34:50.382 --> 34:52.315
that what they're really
meant for is coming home.

34:52.351 --> 34:54.484
Now, you see? How on earth am I supposed

34:54.518 --> 34:56.485
to come up with something
as good as that?

34:56.521 --> 34:58.521
Because you already did.

34:59.372 --> 35:01.558
Martha, I got that line from you!

35:02.208 --> 35:03.627
I don't remember

35:03.662 --> 35:05.695
ever being that wise and sentimental.

35:05.731 --> 35:07.831
We were driving back
from a long weekend away.

35:08.465 --> 35:12.002
What you said gave me... my theme.

35:12.552 --> 35:14.671
I built my entire speech around that.

35:14.706 --> 35:17.574
So... I was your inspiration?

35:17.609 --> 35:21.511
Was, are and always will be.

35:21.546 --> 35:24.514
Well then, maybe I still have it in me!

35:24.549 --> 35:26.549
Now I probably
won't be very good company,

35:26.585 --> 35:29.019
but now that I'm bursting
with brilliance,

35:29.054 --> 35:30.820
I've gotta write it all down.

35:30.856 --> 35:32.689
I am sure that whatever you say

35:32.724 --> 35:34.524
will be remembered for years to come.

35:34.559 --> 35:36.526
Oh, I just feel badly

35:36.561 --> 35:39.863
that no one will remember your
speech once they hear mine.

35:42.100 --> 35:44.601
♪♪♪

35:50.075 --> 35:52.542
Are we out of lavender mint tea already?

35:52.577 --> 35:54.377
No, I moved it. I thought

35:54.413 --> 35:56.846
anything mint should go with the candies.

35:56.882 --> 35:59.022
- Oh...
- Hi, Sam.

35:59.057 --> 36:03.019
- Hello! Hey.
- Hi.

36:03.055 --> 36:05.055
I was just on my way back to
the office. Thought I'd stop in

36:05.090 --> 36:07.791
and find out, are we going with
a sit-down dinner or a buffet?

36:07.826 --> 36:10.293
- For our wedding?
- I know we already decided on

36:10.329 --> 36:12.395
that jazz trio for the music,
and I was thinking,

36:12.431 --> 36:14.464
"Maybe they could play through
dinner." And then I realized,

36:14.499 --> 36:16.366
we haven't even talked about
what we're having yet.

36:16.401 --> 36:18.401
Oh. Well, I didn't know you'd wanted to.

36:18.437 --> 36:20.737
Well, yeah. Of course.
Let's start thinking

36:20.772 --> 36:23.106
- about the options.
- Of course.

36:33.652 --> 36:35.752
Sam's already making plans?

36:35.787 --> 36:37.954
Yeah, I guess he is.

36:38.596 --> 36:40.590
Except it's hard to tell

36:40.625 --> 36:42.592
if what he's doing is what you want.

36:42.627 --> 36:45.261
Hmm. Yeah, I'm not sure that it is.

36:45.297 --> 36:47.664
Well, you know, a good marriage

36:47.699 --> 36:49.427
takes great communication,

36:49.462 --> 36:51.668
but you can't expect
the other person to just know

36:51.703 --> 36:54.471
what you want. You actually
have to tell them.

36:54.506 --> 36:58.441
- Well, that's good advice.
- It is. And it's exactly

36:58.477 --> 37:00.910
what you told me right before
I married Brandon.

37:02.647 --> 37:04.781
I guess I did say that.

37:04.816 --> 37:07.851
Oh, and I put the tea
back in the right place,

37:07.886 --> 37:10.286
exactly the way you wanted it.

37:10.322 --> 37:12.622
♪♪♪

37:18.910 --> 37:21.645
- Hi, Mom.
- Hi.

37:21.680 --> 37:24.187
Did you get those games
over to the hospital?

37:24.222 --> 37:25.685
We did.

37:26.035 --> 37:28.303
We ran into Courtney.

37:28.339 --> 37:31.340
Really? How did Nick do with that?

37:31.375 --> 37:33.342
He said some good things.

37:33.377 --> 37:36.111
A lot of good things.

37:36.147 --> 37:39.014
Well, sometimes that happens
when we give people a chance.

37:39.050 --> 37:41.183
And I guess that's what I should've
done in the first place, right?

37:42.243 --> 37:43.852
I know you were just trying

37:43.888 --> 37:47.056
to help two people that you
care about very much.

37:48.511 --> 37:50.859
Yeah, except you would have
managed to do all of that

37:50.895 --> 37:53.162
without everything
blowing up in your face.

37:53.197 --> 37:54.846
How are you supposed to know

37:54.882 --> 37:57.034
when to say things out loud

37:57.069 --> 37:59.034
and when to say nothing at all?

37:59.070 --> 38:01.703
It's just something
that comes with experience

38:01.739 --> 38:04.321
and experience comes with time.

38:04.322 --> 38:06.823
There's no way
to make it come any faster?

38:07.857 --> 38:10.523
Impatience is something
that all the young Merriwicks

38:10.558 --> 38:12.077
have struggled with,

38:12.112 --> 38:14.831
along with knowing
the difference between what we

38:14.866 --> 38:19.535
can do... and whether
or not we should do it.

38:20.782 --> 38:23.139
OK, that was a regular deck of cards

38:23.174 --> 38:25.318
and Nick picked the shelf himself.

38:25.353 --> 38:26.788
Hmm.

38:28.873 --> 38:30.646
OK. I might've Merriwicked

38:30.682 --> 38:32.648
things up a little
to make sure that things

38:32.684 --> 38:35.017
turned out the way that I wanted them to.

38:35.053 --> 38:38.054
- That is the easier way, isn't it?
- Easier than what?

38:38.466 --> 38:40.289
Than doing the real work.

38:41.427 --> 38:42.658
So let's make sure

38:42.694 --> 38:44.675
we both remember when we need to do that.

38:44.700 --> 38:48.164
Yeah. Thanks, Mom.

38:48.199 --> 38:50.900
♪♪♪

39:03.882 --> 39:05.915
(SIGHING)

39:08.233 --> 39:09.488
- Oh, hey!
- Hi.

39:09.513 --> 39:12.889
I was just gonna slap a little
paint on these baseboards

39:12.924 --> 39:15.358
- if I'm not in your way.
- Oh, no. That's fine.

39:22.927 --> 39:24.894
Except, you know what?

39:25.069 --> 39:28.004
I actually don't need that done.

39:28.600 --> 39:29.872
Are you sure?

39:29.908 --> 39:32.074
Yeah. Yeah, I...

39:32.110 --> 39:35.678
I like the way they look.
I want them to stay that way.

39:35.713 --> 39:38.447
Oh. I guess I should have asked

39:38.483 --> 39:40.750
before I spent so much time down there.

39:40.785 --> 39:43.614
- And I should have told you.
- Oh, that's OK.

39:43.649 --> 39:47.056
I found 43 cents behind the
couches, so I came out ahead.

39:47.091 --> 39:48.925
- Thanks.
- Hey, Sam.

39:48.960 --> 39:53.062
Hi, George. So, I...
got some options for dates.

39:53.097 --> 39:54.964
Oh, Sam, you don't have to do that.

39:54.999 --> 39:57.566
I just thought we should
start nailing things down.

39:57.602 --> 39:59.772
Sam...

39:59.807 --> 40:01.804
I can't wait to get married.

40:01.839 --> 40:04.707
I'm looking forward to it
more than I can say.

40:06.577 --> 40:09.745
But I don't know why we have to
make all these decisions right now.

40:09.781 --> 40:12.048
Just trying to stay ahead of the curve.

40:12.083 --> 40:15.084
Except you haven't asked me what I want,

40:15.119 --> 40:17.086
and I haven't told you.

40:17.649 --> 40:19.088
That's true.

40:19.123 --> 40:21.090
Both those things are true.

40:21.735 --> 40:24.427
I just want things
to start out right this time.

40:24.495 --> 40:26.495
Well, everything's off
to a pretty great start.

40:26.531 --> 40:28.965
I want our marriage
to be different. With Linda...

40:29.000 --> 40:30.933
I was hardly involved at all.

40:30.969 --> 40:33.602
She made most of the decisions,
and I just kind of...

40:33.638 --> 40:36.372
went along. I don't even
remember helping with any

40:36.407 --> 40:39.275
of the planning. I just showed
up in a tux and said, "I do."

40:39.712 --> 40:41.310
OK. So this time,

40:41.346 --> 40:43.679
we'll make all those decisions together.

40:45.350 --> 40:48.451
But... I don't think

40:48.486 --> 40:50.953
that we have to set
anything in stone right now.

40:50.989 --> 40:52.655
I want to be able to

40:52.690 --> 40:55.424
walk past a field of flowers and say,

40:55.460 --> 40:57.626
"That's the exact colour I want."

40:57.662 --> 41:00.129
Or stumble upon a hidden beach

41:00.164 --> 41:04.200
and decide, "This is where we
should say our vows."

41:06.170 --> 41:07.573
I like that.

41:08.950 --> 41:10.827
We can do that.

41:12.578 --> 41:14.343
There is one thing

41:14.379 --> 41:17.146
that I am ready to decide right now.

41:17.181 --> 41:20.116
- Hmm.
- Hmm.

41:21.652 --> 41:25.154
I want this to be the song
that's played at our ceremony.

41:25.189 --> 41:27.556
- Me too.
- Hmm.

41:29.193 --> 41:32.495
♪♪♪

41:40.104 --> 41:43.512
Well, well. I thought you two
might play well together.

41:43.548 --> 41:45.708
Ah, yes, we do.

41:45.743 --> 41:47.977
All it takes is a little practice.

41:48.012 --> 41:51.367
(DOORBELL RINGING) I'll get it.

41:56.888 --> 41:58.988
Dad.

